[Note "1:control"]
[Note "2:control"]
[Note "3:2 keycards + trump Q"]
{[show S]
How do you open the bidding?[BID 1S]
With 18 HCP and a balanced hand, you open 1\S.  Partner responds  2\H. What do you rebid?[BID 3H]
You know this is a 5-card suit, and bid 3\H, confirming the 8+card trump fit and sets the trump suit.
Partner rebids 3\S, a control bid, showing first or second round control.  (Some will play this as showing 3-card support for spades, but I recommend playing this as a control bid.). What do you bid now? [BID 4C]
You bid 4C, also a control bid, showing first or second round control in clubs.  Partner bids 4NT, a keycard request using 1430.  What do you respond? [BID 5S]
[show NS]
You bid 5\s, showing two keycards and the trump queen.  Partner bids the slam.
The slam is a good one. If either the \SQ or \CK is right there are 12 tricks by way of a finesse. But the best way to play the hand would be to try to establish a \S in the South hand, and if that fails try the \C finesse.}

