{[show S]
North opens 1\H - how should you respond?[bid 2C]
North rebids 2NT.  How do you continue?[bid 3NT]
South shows her minimum by bidding 3NT.
North continues with 4NT - what does this mean?  How do you continue?[BID 6NT]
[show NS]
 North's 4NT was not Blackwood, but rather a quantitative raise in Notrump, and an invitation to slam.
You have 15 points, and they are good ones. So you accept the invitation and bid 6NT.
There are 11 top tricks. A 3-3 \H split would provide the 12th winner, but this is against the odds. Better to try two \S finesses, a 75% chance.}

