1S Pass 1NT Pass 2S Pass 3S Pass 4S Pass Pass Pass
{[show S]
North opens 1\S. What do you respond? [bid 1NT]
With 11 points you cannot respond 2\C. So you bid 1NT, which is forcing for 1 round. 
North rebids 2\s, promising at least 6 \ss and denying a 4-card side suit.
What do you bid now? [bid 3s]
[show NS]
You are strong enough to invite to game, and with the known 8-card fit you say 3\S.
North has a little extra so he bids 4\S, which is a pretty good contract.}

