[Student "S"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/two_over_one"]
[Auction "S"]
1S Pass 1NT Pass 2C Pass 3S Pass Pass Pass
{[show S]
How do you start the bidding on this hand? [bid 1s]
You open 1\s.  Partner responds 1NT, forcing for one round.  What do you rebid? [bid 2c]
You rebid 2\C, a 3-card suit. North now jumps to 3\S, showing limit-raise strength. This sequence is the way to show a limit-raise with only 3 trumps; an immediate jump-raise to the 3-level shows a limit-raise with 4 trumps.
What do you bid now? [bid pass]
In any case you have a bare minimum and pass the invitation.
[show NS]}